Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Mini Cucumber{1} lengthwise; lay flat and cut into ½-inch-thick sticks. Trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Apple{1}. Halve @Orange{1}; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Cut @Fresh Mozzarella{4%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

Place @Cream Cheese{4%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until softened, ~{15-30%seconds}.

Add @Buttermilk Ranch Dressing{1.5%ounce} to bowl and whisk to combine.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Lay tortillas on a clean work surface.

Evenly spread ranch sauce over tortillas. Add as many @Shredded Carrots{4%ounce} as you like to bottom two-thirds of each tortilla; top with cucumber sticks and lettuce leaves. Lightly season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create roll-ups. Halve roll-ups on a diagonal.

To serve: Divide veggie roll-ups between plates and serve with apple slices, orange slices, mozzarella, and @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%ounce} on the side.

To stash: Refrigerate veggie roll-ups, apple slices, orange slices, and mozzarella in separate containers and pack as desired!